You can use a simple formula to make a safe password (probably).
1) Choose at least three words. EG: CharlieBirdRed
2) Take one letter at a fixed point in each word, and replace it with its number in the alphabet. EG: 3harlie2ird18ed
3) Replace some of the numbers with the character that corresponds to it. EG: 3harlie@ird18ed

This specific password would take 33 Million Years to crack. Since this password formula is easily modifiable, it would be hard for somebody to crack, even if they knew which words you were using as your base words.
